25/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Boris Tadic described Wednesday's (24 September) shooting of a Serbian Army officer as "a new terrorist attack by Albanian extremists". Army Major Rahman Bandic, traveling in a military vehicle near the village of Dobrosin in southern Serbia, was ambushed and seriously wounded. Ambassador Maurizio Massari, the OSCE mission head in Serbia-Montenegro, also blamed the incident on terrorists trying to destabilise the region. (B92, Tanjug, BBC, FoNet, OSCE - 24/09/03)
